    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-01-25T16:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-01-25T16:45:00-05:00" n="728"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d728">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.452/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-25T16:00:00-05:45"
                            >January 25, 1929—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. Department’s 11, January 25, 3 p.m.<note n="60" xml:id="d728fn60">Not
                        printed; it requested the Minister to cable full text of law.</note> Full
                    text of the law of January 4th as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <list>
                            <item>“Article 1. That the admiral commanding the squadron of the United
                                States Navy on vigilance service in the waters of Nicaragua and the
                                high officials with grade of general in the American armed forces
                                who are in command of the American mission of pacification, <pb
                                    facs="0762" n="644" xml:id="pg_644"/> will be accorded, for the
                                purposes of protocol and courtesy, the rank of ministers
                                plenipotentiary and envoys extraordinary of the United States on
                                special mission near the Government of the Republic of
                                Nicaragua.</item>
                            <item>Article 2. This decree will come into force from its publication
                                by <hi rend="italic">bando.</hi>”<note n="*" xml:id="d728fn61">i. e.
                                    by oral proclamation. [Notation on original in ink in the
                                    handwriting of Assistant Secretary of State Francis
                                    White.]</note>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
